body:
I found this when I was writing code for [tera](https://github.com/Keats/tera/blob/869bbce6bbbe7b572ca3294ab4bdbb18df148705/src/template.rs#L47) that was designed to remove an unnecessary `clone`.

Code reproduced below:
```rust
match node {
    block @ Node::Block { .. } => {
        let string;
        let children;

        if let Node::Block { ref name, ref body } = block {
            if blocks.contains_key(name) {
                bail!("Block `{}` is duplicated", name);
            }
            string = name.to_string();
            children = body.get_children();
        } else {
            unreachable!();
        };

        blocks.insert(string, block);
        find_blocks(children, blocks)?;
    },
    // ...
}
```

Inside the match branch, an `if let` statement with an unreachable else branch is required, whereas a simple `let` binding should do.
